vectorData.altText: That's right! Notice the pyramids on the ventral aspect and the inferior cerebellar peduncles reaching posteriorly but they are not continuous with the cerebellum. Notice also the fourth ventricle between the inferior cerebellar peduncles.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Many of these features are easily identifiable in MRI. In this image of the caudal pons, identify:
the medullary pyramids, anteriorly
the location of the olives, posterolateral to the pyramids
the inferior cerebellar peduncles, “reaching” posteriorly
the fourth ventricle posteriorly, between the medulla and cerebellum
